{{Infobox video game |title = Blitzkrieg 2 |image = Blitzkrieg 2 Cover.jpg |developer = [[Nival Interactive]] |publisher = [[CDV Software]] |designer = |series = ''[[Blitzkrieg (video game series)|Blitzkrieg]]'' |released = {{vgrelease|NA|October 2, 2005}} |genre = [[Real-time tactics]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] }}
'''''Blitzkrieg 2''''' ({{lang-ru|Блицкриг II|italic=yes}}) is a [[real-time tactics]] computer game based on the events of [[World War II]], the game is an evolution of its predecessor ''[[Blitzkrieg (video game)|Blitzkrieg]]'' and is the second title in the [[Blitzkrieg (video game series)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/blitzkrieg-2/|title=Blitzkrieg 2|website=[[GamesRadar]]|date=September 8, 2005 |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> The game takes place in [[North African Campaign|North Africa]], the [[Asiatic-Pacific Theater|Pacific]] and [[European theatre of World War II|Europe]], and features the 6 different factions portrayed in the game that fought in their battle respective grounds during the war.
==Gameplay== As its predecessor and the similar ''[[Sudden Strike]] ''games, ''Blitzkrieg 2 ''focuses on the battles of [[World War II]] rather than [[real-time strategy]] aspects like base building and resource extraction.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/blitzkrieg-ii-updated-impressions-whats-new/1100-6127480/|title=Blitzkrieg II Updated Impressions - What's New|website=[[GameSpot]]|date=June 14, 2005|author=Andrew Park|accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> The game features many new features and units over its predecessor; the graphics engine is upgraded, allowing for full 3D and the game features over 250 units compared to ''Blitzkrieg'''s 200.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/blitzkrieg-ii-demo-offers-three-offensives/1100-6132533/|author=Tim Surette|title=Blitzkrieg II demo offers three offensives|website=GameSpot|date=September 2, 2005|accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> In Blitzkrieg 2, you can choose from three separate campaigns: The Nazi German Campaign, the American Campaign, and the Soviet Campaign, each divided into four distinct chapters. The German campaign begins in France, 1940, where you are put in command of German offensive forces in an effort to [[Battle of France|conquer France]]. Here, you may use the signature [[Blitzkrieg]] strategy. The second chapter is set in [[North African Campaign|North Africa]], which ends with your [[Siege of Tobruk|capture of Tobruk]]. The third is in the Soviet Union, during [[Case Blue]]. And finally, the fourth chapter is staged in the [[Ardennes]] during the [[Battle of the Bulge]], 1944. The American campaign has its first 3 chapters in the [[Pacific Theater (World War II)|Pacific theater]], where you lead your forces against the IJA ([[Imperial Japanese Army]]) and IJN ([[Imperial Japanese Navy]]) in a number of missions beginning shortly after the [[attack on Pearl Harbor]]. The final chapter of the American campaign is in the German [[Ruhr]], 1945. The Soviet Campaign begins shortly after [[Operation Barbarossa]], going through the 5 years of the war against Germany eventually ending with your capture of the German capital of [[Battle of Berlin|Berlin]]. At the end of each campaign, a short cinematic plays.
The game contains six factions: *[[Nazi Germany|Germany]] *[[Soviet Union]] *[[United Kingdom]] *[[Empire of Japan|Japan]] *[[United States]] *[[French Third Republic|France]] Japan was newly added for ''Blitzkrieg 2 ''for the new Pacific theatre, however, it had previously made a minor appearance in Blitzkrieg: Rolling Thunder. The game also includes an encyclopedia of all units, so you can easily read about the units you get to see in-game. There is an online version of this at the [http://www.blitzkrieg2.de/index.php?page=blitz2-10-2 ''Blitzkrieg 2 ''website].
The game has relatively low [[system requirements]] considering its graphics and capabilities.<ref>[http://gamesystemrequirements.com/games.php?id=680 Blitzkrieg 2 System Requirements] Retrieved January 23, 2014</ref>
==Reception== The game received positive reviews before release.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/blitzkrieg-ii-e3-2005-impressions/1100-6126177/|author=Matthew Rorie|title=Blitzkrieg II E3 2005 Impressions|website=GameSpot|date=May 20, 2005}}</ref> Yet never achieved the same long lived success its predecessor had achieved, even though two expansions and numerous spin offs were made.
{{Video game reviews | title = Blitzkrieg | state = released | MC = 75/100 <ref name=Metacritic/> | 1UP = C+<ref name=1up/> | GSpy = 2.5/5<ref name=GameSpy/> | IGN = 8.4/10<ref name=IGN/> }}
== Addons == The base game Blitzkrieg 2 was released together with both add-ons as ''Blitzkrieg 2 Anthology''. * '''''Blitzkrieg 2: Fall Of The Reich''''': the first [[expansion pack]] was released on February 20, 2007.<ref>[http://www.ign.com/games/blitzkrieg-ii-fall-of-the-reich/pc-824567 Blitzkrieg 2: Fall Of The Reich]. IGN. Retrieved January 23, 2014</ref> * '''''Blitzkrieg 2: Liberation''''': the second Another expansion pack was released on October 12, 2007 in the [[European Union|EU]].<ref>[http://www.ign.com/games/blitzkrieg-2-liberation/pc-955384 Blitzkrieg 2: Liberation]. IGN. Retrieved January 23, 2014</ref>
== Spin-off games == * '''''Frontline: Fields of Thunder''''': this spin-off was released on April 9, 2007 at a retail price of $29.99 USD.<ref>[http://www.ign.com/games/frontline-fields-of-thunder/pc-856797 Frontline: Fields of Thunder]. IGN. Retrieved January 23, 2014</ref> * '''''Great Battles: Battle of Tobruk''''' by the company Arise Games was one of various other spin-offs of which however, some were released exclusively in Russia, Nival Interactive's home country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arisegames.com/en/projects_tobruk.html |title=Great Battles: Battle of Tobruk |publisher=Arise |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903051523/http://www.arisegames.com/en/projects_tobruk.html |archivedate=2014-09-03 |df= }}</ref>
