{{Infobox software |title = Dust Racing 2D |screenshot = Dust Racing 2D 2.0.0 Intro.png |developer = Jussi Lind |released = {{Start date and age|2012}} | latest release version = 2.0.0 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2017|12|24|df=no}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = |genre = Local Play (1-2 players) [[Racing game|Racing]] |platform = [[Linux]], [[Windows]] |license = [[GNU GPLv3]] |website =https://juzzlin.github.io/DustRacing2D/ |repo=https://github.com/juzzlin/DustRacing2D }}
'''Dust Racing 2D''' (dustrac) is an [[open-source software|open-source]], tile-based 2D racing game developed by Jussi Lind. The [[source code]] is licensed under [[GNU GPLv3]].
== Gameplay== The purpose of the game is to race against eleven challenging computer players on different race tracks. Finishing in TOP 6 will unlock a new race track. Only a small portion of the race track is visible on the scrolling screen. There's also an option for a [[split screen (computer graphics)|split-screen]] two player game. Dust Racing 2D comes with a [[level editor]] that makes creating new race tracks easy.
== History == ''Dust Racing 2D'' was inspired by [[Super Cars]] and [[Slicks ’n’ Slide]]. The game was built by Jussi Lind on [[Qt (framework)|Qt]] development framework and it uses [[OpenGL]] for graphics. Due to the source availability it is possible to port the game to [[Cross-platform|multiple operating systems]].<ref name="Softpedia" /> The first version of the game was published in 2012. The game is under continued development as of August 2017.
== Reception == ''Dust Racing 2D'' was selected in Christmas 2013 and in August 2015 as "HotPick" by [[Linux Format]].<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/Linux_Format_178_Christmas_2013/#page/n63/mode/2up/search/hotgames Linux Format 178 Christmas 2013] page 59</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/stream/Linux_Format_August_2015_UK/#page/n59/mode/2up/search/hotgames Linux Format 200 August 2015] page 60</ref> Dust Racing 2D was reviewed by [[Softpedia]] as being ''"All in all, Dust Racing 2D proved to be a fun video game, especially for nostalgics who want to relive their childhood."'' with 4 of 5 points.<ref name="Softpedia"> {{cite web |url=http://linux.softpedia.com/get/GAMES-ENTERTAINMENT/Arcade/Dust-Racing-2D-96657.shtml | title=A car racing game written in Qt and geared towards Linux, BSD, Windows and Mac users |last1=Nestor |first1=Marius |date=2015-04-29 | work=Review |publisher=[[Softpedia]] |access-date=2015-04-29 |quote=}}</ref> Dust Racing 2D is provided by several [[freeware]] outlets which aggregated around 40,000 downloads.<ref>[https://sourceforge.net/projects/dustrac/files/stats/timeline?dates=2000-05-18+to+2017-05-24 stats] on [[sourceforge.net]]</ref><ref>[http://www.computerbild.de/download/Dust-Racing-2D-8055218.html Dust racing 2D] on [[computerbild.de]]</ref><ref>[http://www.majorgeeks.com/files/details/dust_racing_2d.html dust racing 2d] on [[majorgeeks.com]]</ref>
