'''''Shadazzle''''' is a British [[comedy-drama]] [[web series]] following a group of friends, inspired by soap operas.<ref name="Tubefilter">{{Citation|last=Gutelle|first=Sam|title=Indie Spotlight: 'Neighborhood Watchmen' Puts Heroes in 'The Office'|work=Tubefilter|date=2013-10-11|url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2013/10/11/indie-spotlight-neighborhood-watchmen/}}</ref> The show was created by Brett Barnett and Stacey Mackenzie and premiered on 25 January 2012. The series is filmed primarily in [[Wombwell]]<ref name="Robinson">{{cite episode|title=Rony Robinson, 06/08/2012|episodelink =|url =|series=Rony Robinson|serieslink =|credits=Presenter: Rony Robinson|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC Radio Sheffield]]|location=[[Sheffield]]|airdate=2012-08-06}}</ref> and [[Sheffield]], with exteriors shot in [[Wath-upon-Dearne]].<ref name="Advertiser">{{cite news|title=Shadazzle Pricking the Soaps Bubble|work=The Rotherham Advertiser|first=Claire|last=Johnson|date=6 July 2012|page=37}}</ref>
==Synopsis== A parody of over-the-top [[soap operas]], ''Shadazzle'' follows the melodrama in the lives of a group of friends, centred on Florence Smith (played by Helen Hall) and her fiancé, Fred Flagglebush (Brett Barnett).<ref name="Chronicle">{{cite news|title=Friends write and star in local soap|work=The Barnsley Chronicle - 'Chronicle 2' supplement|first=Paul|last=Nizinskyj|date=3 August 2012|page=3}}</ref> When Fred decides to hire a "vodka swilling cleaner,"<ref name="Flicker">{{Citation|last =Duncan|first =Sarah|title =Shadazzle|newspaper =Flicker Magazine|pages =|year =2012}}</ref> the couple's personal expenses become tighter and Florence is forced to accept a job as an exotic dancer at a local club.<ref name="Terrace" /> She soon becomes the center of an unstable Trevor Shaw's (Jonathan Homer) unwanted affection, that ends in disaster when Trevor crashes the wedding.<ref name="Terrace" />
Later seasons explore romance, loneliness, and ultimately the murder of Alex Abernathy (Leigh-Anne Homer) and the clash between Florence and her murderer, Billy (Ellis Marsh), all told from the perspectives of Florence and those closest to her.<ref name="Terrace" />
Each episode of ''Shadazzle'' follows the perspective of a different character, with story lines eventually interlinking as the series progresses,<ref name="WebVee">{{Citation|last =Clarke|first =Susan E.|title =Shadazzle|newspaper =WebVee Guide|pages =|year =2014|url =http://webveeguide.com/blog/2014/02/shadazzle}}</ref> and features themes of personal struggle and alcoholism, among others.<ref name="SnobbyRobot">{{Citation|last =Urtz|first =Eric|title =Shadazzle|newspaper =Snobby Robot|pages =|year =2012|url =http://snobbyrobot.com/2012/11/08/web-series-wednesday-shadazzle/}}</ref>
