{{for|the 2004 video game|WRC 4}} {{Infobox video game | title = WRC 4: FIA World Rally Championship | image =WRC4 PS3 cover.jpg | developer = [[Milestone S.r.l.]] | publisher = {{vgrelease|[[Europe|EU]] / [[North America|NA]]|[[Bigben Interactive]]}}{{vgrelease|JP|[[Square Enix]]}} | series = ''[[World Rally Championship (video game series)|World Rally Championship]]'' | platforms = [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation Vita]], [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Xbox 360]] | released = {{Video game release|EU|October 25, 2013|JP|July 24, 2014 (PS3, Vita)|NA|July 29, 2014 (PS3, Vita)}} | genre = [[Racing video game|Racing]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] | designer = Sébastien Pellicano }}
'''''WRC 4: FIA World Rally Championship''''' is the official [[racing video game]] of the [[2013 World Rally Championship season]]. It was developed by [[Milestone S.r.l.]] being the last WRC Videogame to be developed by Milestone. ''WRC 4'' was released in Europe on 25 October 2013.
Per the calendar, [[Rally New Zealand]] was removed from the previous game, while [[Rallye Deutschland]] and [[Rally Mexico]] both had revised routes.
==Reception== {{Video game reviews |GR=57.50%<ref name="GR">http://www.gamerankings.com/ps3/734964-wrc-4-fia-world-rally-championship/index.html</ref> |MC=63/100<ref name="MC">http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/wrc-4-fia-world-rally-championship</ref> |OPMUK=5/10 |OPMAU=65% |EuroG=60% |IGN=80% |GSpot=6/10 |OXMUK=70% }} The game had mixed reviews. The general consensus is that "the career mode is a lot of fun and the tracks are varied. On the other hand, the game lacks challenge, has an overabundance of loading times and disappoints audiovisually." It got to number 21 in the UK sales charts.<ref>http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fsoftware%2Fuk%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=110031&arch=t&lyr=2013&year=2013&week=43</ref>
